news.title: OSB's director faces FIR for fund misuse & licence violations in Gurugram
news.para: Haryana authorities have filed an FIR against Ocean Seven Buildtech and its director, Swaraj Singh, for financial fraud and license violations in affordable housing projects. The company allegedly collected payments without completing construction, leading to stalled projects and financial distress for buyers.

news.title: Karnataka's decision to increase property registration fee triggers backlash
news.para: Karnataka's decision to increase property registration fees by 2% has triggered widespread opposition. Arvind Bellad criticized the move as an "anti-people policy," burdening citizens already struggling with rising costs. The fee hike, raising total charges to 7.6%, has stalled property transactions in Dharwad.

news.title: Noida: Homebuyers hold protest over incomplete project, delayed possession
news.para: More than 80 homebuyers of the incomplete Lotus Arena project in Noida protested against the delayed possession, citing misuse of funds by old promoters and subsequent delays due to Noida Authority's block on revalidation.

news.title: Access road to Gurugram's sector 85 township closed, buyers protest against builder
news.para: Gurugram residents of Orris Carnation, Aster Court, and Aster Court Premier protested the closure of a promised access road. The residents marched to Iris Broadway Mall. They claimed the blocked road forces them to use a congested village road, increasing travel time and posing safety risks. Residents are demanding immediate action from authorities.

news.title: Lack of GPS-mapping puts Pune civic body's properties at risk of misuse
news.para: Pune's ambitious project, initiated in 2021-22 to map 3,000 civic properties using GPS for protection against encroachment, remains incomplete after five years. Activists claim the project stalled despite awarding a tender. The PMC estate department says groundwork restarted six months ago, expanding the project's scope.

news.title: UP minister says registry of flats in Noida can be okayed immediately once NOC is cleared
news.para: UP Minister Ravindra Jaiswal clarifies that property registration delays in Noida and Greater Noida stem from disputes between builders and development authorities over NOCs. He emphasized that the registration department promptly processes registrations once builders obtain the necessary NOCs from the Noida, Greater Noida, or Yamuna Expressway authorities, highlighting their lack of involvement in the delays.

news.title: Ludhiana development body asks defaulters to pay dues or lose plots
news.para: Glada is issuing notices to defaulting allottees of residential and commercial plots in its urban estates, warning them of property loss if dues aren't settled promptly. Allotments for SCO 104 and SCO 03 in Dugri Phase-1 have already been cancelled.

news.title: Ghaziabad has 300 more hectares where illegal colonies may come up
news.para: Ghaziabad faces a growing challenge as non-conforming land use has expanded by 301 hectares in the latest Master Plan 2031, signaling a surge in unplanned development and potentially fueling the proliferation of illegal colonies. The city now has 1,391 hectares classified as non-conforming land, prompting GDA to conduct a survey of these zones.

news.title: Over 200 projects register with UP-RERA in first eight months of 2025
news.para: Uttar Pradesh RERA witnessed registration of 208 projects between January and August 2025, indicating positive investor sentiment. Lucknow and Gautambuddha Nagar led in project registrations. Enhanced monitoring by RERA ensures timely project completion, promoter accountability, and increased consumer confidence in the real estate market.

news.title: Madras HC flays Chennai civic body for delay in sealing buildings
news.para: Madras High Court criticized Greater Chennai Corporation (GCC) for its "negligent and indolent" approach in enforcing lock-and-seal notices on unauthorized constructions. The court noted GCC was allowing building occupants to seek alternative legal options instead of executing court orders.

news.title: Access roads missing? OCs to be denied for projects: Haryana minister
news.para: Haryana government is addressing builder misconduct. Developers mislead homebuyers about road access. New policies will ensure adherence to norms. Occupancy certificates will be denied for unbuilt roads. On-ground verification is now mandatory. The government prioritizes resident interests. Approvals will clarify road rights. This will boost buyer confidence. It will also curb irregularities. Residents currently face access issues.

news.title: K Raheja eyes 1.5-acre South Mumbai's iconic Famous Studios parcel in ₹650 crore agreement
news.para: Famous Studios, a landmark in South Mumbai since 1946, is likely to change ownership. K Raheja Corp is in advanced discussions to acquire the 1.5-acre property. The deal is structured as a joint development agreement. It has a development potential of around 4 lakh sq ft. Piramal Realty's previous attempt to redevelop the studio failed.

news.title: Over 140 unauthorised structures in Vasai-Virar region will be demolished post Ganpati festival: Maharashtra minister
news.para: Following the tragic building collapse in Virar East that resulted in 17 fatalities, Maharashtra Minister Ganesh Naik announced the demolition of 141 unauthorized buildings across the Vasai-Virar region after the Ganpati festival. Naik emphasized the need for strict action against illegal constructions and promised to address the rehabilitation of affected residents with the Chief Minister.

news.title: Delhi government to set up portal for investors to identify land parcels
news.para: To boost ease of doing business, the Delhi government is developing a centralised online Delhi Land Bank Portal. This platform will assist investors in identifying suitable land parcels for industrial and infrastructure projects. DSIIDC will develop the portal with geospatial data from GSDL, streamlining land allotment and reducing bureaucratic delays.

news.title: Ranchi civic body lists government institutions among major property tax defaulters
news.para: The Ranchi Municipal Corporation (RMC) is struggling with massive property tax defaults, primarily from government entities, totaling thousands of crores. Major defaulters include HEC, South Eastern Railway, and the Sports Authority of Jharkhand, crippling the RMC's finances. The RMC is considering legal action to recover the dues, while locals criticize the lack of accountability and its impact on city services.

news.title: PWD selects seven sites for redevelopment project under PPP model in Delhi
news.para: The Public Works Department (PWD) in Delhi has identified seven residential land parcels for redevelopment and commercialization under a PPP model. These locations, including Vikas Bhawan-1 and colonies in Gulabi Bagh and Kalyanvas, will be redeveloped to meet future housing needs and optimize land use.

news.title: Ludhiana civic body urges residents to pay property tax as deadline looms
news.para: The Ludhiana municipal corporation is making a final push to collect outstanding property tax by offering a one-time settlement (OTS) policy, which waives all penalties and interest. The deadline for the scheme is August 31st. To facilitate last-minute payments, suvidha kendras will remain open on Saturday and Sunday, providing residents a golden opportunity to clear their dues.

news.title: MicroMitti to invest ₹300 crore to develop IT Park in Indore
news.para: MicroMitti, a proptech co-investment real estate firm, is set to invest ₹300 crore in developing a high-rise IT Park on Indore’s Super Corridor. This project marks the first privately built initiative approved under the Madhya Pradesh IT Policy 2025.

news.title: Telangana government prepares for forensic audit of land records
news.para: Telangana is gearing up for a forensic audit of its land records, with Telangana Technology Services Limited (TGTS) expected to sign an agreement with a Kerala-based security audit agency within a week. The audit will initially focus on suspicious land transactions in districts like Rangareddy and Hyderabad.

news.title: SC dismisses appeal challenging eviction orders issued by HYDRAA
news.para: The Supreme Court has dismissed businessman P Satya Narayana's appeal against eviction orders, affirming the Jubilee Hills House Building Cooperative Society's right to reclaim a 2,000-square-yard property in Jubilee Hills. This decision follows a Telangana High Court ruling that supported HYDRAA's eviction notices due to Satya Narayana's failure to provide ownership proof for the land.
